&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree (or higher) from an accredited university in Health Physics, Nuclear Engineering, a related physical science (e.g., Physics, Chemistry), or engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OR Equivalent education and/or extensive, progressive experience (e.g., 10+ years as a senior HPT/RPT or Naval ELT) as approved by the RPP Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OR Current certification by the American Board of Health Physics (CHP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of applied, professional experience in operational health physics.&lt;/li&gt;
